namedLocations.description: Chicago (/ʃɪˈkɑːɡoʊ/ , locally also /ʃɪˈkɔːɡoʊ/), officially the City of Chicago, is the most populous city in Illinois, as well as the third most populous city in the United States. With an estimated population of 2,705,994 (2018), it is the most populous city in the Midwest. Chicago is the principal city of the Chicago metropolitan area, often referred to as Chicagoland, and the county seat of Cook County, the second most populous county in the United States. The metropolitan area, at nearly 10 million people, is the third-largest in the United States.

transcript.text: If you can provide a code within 5 minutes versus 30 minutes, you can increase the 21 times of probability of winning a new sale.
Most print companies who works manually are dependent or they're key people or Excel sheets to provide the quotations, whether it's a small volume order or a larger one.

Now according to research, it takes almost 14 to 17 emails to confirm a single order which means it takes a longer time to provide the code and that cost you the loss of opportunities in this tough competition.
While manual estimation process printers need to send the same quotations multiple times for the standard products it means their teams are equipped with the same repetitive tasks.
Also, there is no mechanism or follow up to the send quotations on e-mail and sometimes they miss to process the quotations and ultimately it caused the opportunity loss.
Let me share how you can offer quotes within seconds and also build this strong relationship with your customer helping them to choose right product quantity and pricing.
So, normally print companies get two kinds of inquiries.

1 is for standard products for which they are having standard pricing and another is a custom products which is a unique requirement of a customer and for that customer need to request for the quotation or estimation.
So now let's see how easy it is to set up your products and pricing with advanced formulas in on print shop where you don't need any program or technical knowledge to start with.
So for the standard product, you can set up your complex to simple pricing using our pricing module and then can set up online estimator on your website.
So any team member can instantly offer course in seconds or client can get self estimation online and share quotes on a specific e-mail ID direct from the website.
So it save your time and resources from repetitive activity of estimation as well as customer can get instant response to the request.

Now if your customer ask for any custom products which you do not have pricing ready, still you can categorize your major products and then they can share the details of print via call, e-mail or maybe from website and your team can respond quickly from their phones or desk.

Now you can have a view of all the quotations on a single screen and you can see how many quotations you have responded, how many are in a pending stage yet how many quotations customers have approved or rejected.
So it helps you to strategize your business processes.

Also, if customers approves the court, they or your team can convert that court to order within a single click and it also auto generates the job tickets, shipping labels and assign them to a preferred vendor as well, which has helped our customer to have 90% reduction in the questions tasks during their ordering process and increase their sales.
To improve your estimation and quotation process, connect with us at www.onprintshop.com.
